Durban - Firefighters extinguished a blaze that ripped through a flat at the Merebank Mall, south of Durban on Thursday. Five people were treated at the scene for smoke inhalation, Rescue Care Paramedics said. "Some went to hospital for further care and some refused services after treatment," Rescue Care spokesman, GarrithÂ Jamieson said. The fire started at a flat in Natraj Road road shortly before 10pm.  Sikander Gani, a businessman, said they were busy in their shop when people alerted them to the fire. "He said smoke had been bellowing out from the flats above and they were told to evacuate," He said the mall was closed while firefighters fought the blaze. Daily News